---
// The model presented in two roles: maester (a source that contributes
// docs) and citadel (the aggregator). A maester can be defined in the
// remote repo via `maester.yaml` or declared from the citadel side as a
// "traveling maester" — both end up in the citadel under the same
// publish contract. The deeper compare lives further down in
// `SourceModes.astro`; this section just plants the two-role framing.
//
// Anchor `#how` is the target of the hero's secondary CTA.

import Kicker from './Kicker.astro';
---

<section
  id="how"
  class="section model accent-em"
  aria-labelledby="model-heading"
>
  <header class="section-head">
    <Kicker label="The model" />
    <h2 id="model-heading">Two roles. One contract.</h2>
    <p class="lede">
      Source repositories declare what they publish. One central repository
      pulls them together. A <em>maester</em> can live where the source
      lives — or travel from the citadel to a repo that hasn’t adopted one
      yet.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="role-grid">
    <article class="role role-maester">
      <header class="role-head">
        <svg
          class="role-glyph"
          viewBox="0 0 64 64"
          width="56"
          height="56"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >
          <path
            d="M14 14 H46 a4 4 0 0 1 4 4 v28 a4 4 0 0 1-4 4 H18 a4 4 0 0 1-4-4 V14 a4 4 0 0 1 4-4 a4 4 0 0 1 4 4 v32"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="1.4"></path>
          <path d="M24 22 H42 M24 30 H42 M24 38 H36" stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="1.4" fill="none"></path>
          <circle cx="14" cy="14" r="2" fill="currentColor"></circle>
        </svg>
        <div>
          <p class="role-tag">maester</p>
          <h3>The source that <span class="role-accent">publishes</span></h3>
        </div>
      </header>
      <p>
        A <em>maester</em> is a publish list — a small <code
          >maester.yaml</code
        > that says which files in a repository are worth aggregating.
        It can be defined two ways:
      </p>
      <ul class="role-list">
        <li>
          <span class="role-list-tag">in the source repo</span>
          — drop a <code>maester.yaml</code> at the repo root and the citadel
          consumes whatever it declares.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="role-list-tag alt">in the citadel</span>
          — for repos you don’t control, declare a
          <em>traveling maester</em> in <code>citadel.yaml</code> with an
          <code>includes</code> list. The maester travels to the repo; the
          repo doesn’t change.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <pre class="snippet"><span class="cm"># maester.yaml — in the source repo</span>
<span class="key">schemaVersion:</span> <span class="num">1</span>
<span class="key">documents:</span>
  - <span class="key">path:</span> <span class="str">README.md</span>
  - <span class="key">path:</span> <span class="str">docs/adr/*.md</span>
  - <span class="key">path:</span> <span class="str">docs/runbooks/**/*.md</span></pre>
    </article>

    <article class="role role-citadel">
      <header class="role-head">
        <svg
          class="role-glyph"
          viewBox="0 0 64 64"
          width="56"
          height="56"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >
          <path
            d="M8 56 H56 M14 56 V28 L20 24 L26 28 V56 M28 56 V18 L36 12 L44 18 V56 M46 56 V32 L52 28 L56 30"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="1.4"></path>
          <path
            d="M18 36 V44 M22 36 V44 M34 28 V36 M38 28 V36 M34 42 V50 M38 42 V50 M50 38 V46"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="1.2"></path>
          <path d="M36 12 V6 M34 8 H38" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2"
          ></path>
        </svg>
        <div>
          <p class="role-tag">citadel</p>
          <h3>The repo that <span class="role-accent">gathers</span></h3>
        </div>
      </header>
      <p>
        A <em>citadel</em> is the aggregator: a repository with a
        <code>citadel.yaml</code> that lists every source — resident or
        travelling — and a <code>&lt;baseDir&gt;/</code> tree where their
        content materialises on sync.
      </p>
      <pre class="snippet"><span class="cm"># citadel.yaml</span>
<span class="key">schemaVersion:</span> <span class="num">1</span>
<span class="key">baseDir:</span> <span class="str">context</span>
<span class="key">sources:</span>
  - <span class="key">name:</span> <span class="str">design-system</span>
    <span class="key">url:</span>  <span class="str">github.com/org/design-system</span>
  - <span class="key">name:</span> <span class="str">astro-docs</span>
    <span class="key">url:</span>  <span class="str">github.com/withastro/docs</span>
    <span class="key">includes:</span>
      - <span class="str">src/content/docs/**/*.mdx</span></pre>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .section {
    position: relative;
    max-width: 1180px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5.5rem 2rem;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .section-head {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 0 3.5rem;
  }
  .section-head h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.2vw, 3.25rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .lede {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.55;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .role-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .role {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--surface);
    padding: 1.75rem 1.625rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .role::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 2px;
    background: var(--accent);
  }

  .role-head {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 1.125rem;
  }
  .role-glyph {
    color: var(--accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .role-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    text-transform: lowercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }
  .role h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.1875rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .role-accent {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .role > p {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .role code {
    color: var(--fg);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  /* Resident-vs-traveling sub-list inside the maester card. The mint tag
     marks the in-source variant; the alt-purple tag marks the traveling
     variant — consistent with the SourceModes section further down. */
  .role-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 1.125rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.625rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .role-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }
  .role-list-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: lowercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    border: 1px solid currentColor;
    padding: 0 0.4rem;
    margin-right: 0.375rem;
    vertical-align: 1px;
  }
  .role-list-tag.alt {
    color: var(--accent-alt);
  }

  .snippet {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78125rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
    padding: 0.875rem 1rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--fg);
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
  }
  .snippet .cm {
    color: var(--fg-faint);
  }
  .snippet .key {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .snippet .str {
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .snippet .num {
    color: var(--accent-alt);
  }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .role-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .section {
      padding: 4rem 1.375rem;
    }
  }
</style>
